<Malicious Outlook add-in or COM drop under user profile>
action='createfile' AND filepath startswith '\\Users\\' AND (filepath contains '\\AppData\\Local\\Microsoft\\Outlook\\' || filepath contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\AddIns\\' || filepath contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\COM\\') 
  AND filepath endswith '.dll' OR filepath endswith '.vsto' OR filepath endswith '.addin'
  AND file.signer.exists=false
\\Unsigned DLL/VSTO/ADDIN files written under per-user Outlook/AddIns/COM paths — indicates drop of malicious Outlook add-in or COM component for persistence and mailbox manipulation.
\\MITRE: T1195, T1543.003, T1114

<Outlook.exe spawning scriptable child from Temp/ Roaming (possible loader via attachment)>
parent.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' AND action='createprocess' AND filename.dst IN ('powershell.exe','cscript.exe','wscript.exe','cmd.exe') 
  AND (param.dst contains '%temp%' OR param.dst contains '\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\' OR param.dst contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\')
  AND (param.dst contains '-enc' || param.dst contains '-EncodedCommand' || param.dst contains '.vbs' || param.dst contains '.js')
\\Outlook launching scriptable binaries that reference Temp/Roaming and encoded/embedded scripts — typical of weaponized attachment → loader execution chains.
\\MITRE: T1204.002, T1059.001, T1105

<Outlook process performing atypical outbound HTTP(S) connections (small POSTs / C2-like cadence)>
process.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' AND action='network_connect' AND direction='outbound' 
  AND protocol IN ('HTTP','HTTPS') AND method IN ('POST','PUT') 
  AND count(network_connect) >= 6 within 3600s by host.id AND avg(payload_size) < 2048
\\Outlook making periodic small outbound HTTP(S) posts — suspicious for backdoor C2 using mail-client process to blend with normal traffic.
\\MITRE: T1071.001, T1102

<Unusual mass-send activity via Outlook (many recipients / many attachments within short time)>
process.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' AND action='send_email' AND count(email.recipients) >= 10 within 300s 
  AND count(email.attachments) >= 3 within 300s OR total_attachments_size > 10485760
\\Rapid sending of emails to many recipients with multiple attachments — potential exfil/distribution of harvested data or worm-like propagation through contacts.
\\MITRE: T1041, T1193

<New PST/MSG export created by non-admin process from user Outlook folder>
action='createfile' AND filepath contains '\\Users\\' AND (filepath endswith '.pst' OR filepath endswith '.msg') 
  AND parent.filename.src IN ('OUTLOOK.EXE','powershell.exe','rundll32.exe','cmd.exe') 
  AND file.created_within last 1h
\\Creation of PST/MSG mailbox exports by a process that is not the expected admin backup tool — indicates mailbox/data harvesting for exfiltration.
\\MITRE: T1114, T1537

<Add-in registration via regsvr32 / rundll32 targeting Outlook addin path>
action='createprocess' AND filename.dst IN ('regsvr32.exe','rundll32.exe') 
  AND param.dst contains '\\AppData\\' AND param.dst contains '.dll' 
  AND parent.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' OR parent.directory.src contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\AddIns\\'
\\Use of regsvr32/rundll32 to register or invoke add-in DLLs located in user-writable Outlook add-in paths — suggests COM/Add-in sideloading or execution.
\\MITRE: T1218, T1543.003

<Living-off-the-land download invoked from Outlook context into Temp then executed>
parent.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' AND action='createprocess' AND filename.dst IN ('certutil.exe','bitsadmin.exe','powershell.exe','curl.exe') 
  AND param.dst contains 'http://' OR param.dst contains 'https://' 
  AND param.dst contains '%temp%' OR param.dst contains '\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\' 
  AND later action='createprocess' AND filename.dst NOT IN (trusted_installer_list) within 300s
\\Download-to-temp invoked from an Outlook process or its immediate child followed by execution — indicates staged payload retrieval from a spearphish or malicious link.
\\MITRE: T1105, T1218

<Registry Run key persistence pointing to Outlook-addin-like path in user profile>
action='regmodify' AND reg.path contains 'HKCU\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Run' 
  AND reg.new_value contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\AddIns\\' OR reg.new_value contains '\\AppData\\Local\\Microsoft\\Outlook\\' 
  AND reg.new_value endswith '.dll' OR reg.new_value endswith '.vsto' OR file.signer.exists=false
\\Run key entries pointing to user-profile Outlook/AddIns locations — persistent auto-start for malicious add-in or loader.
\\MITRE: T1547.001, T1543.003

<Process injection indicators where Outlook-originated child writes into other processes>
parent.directory.src contains '\\AppData\\' OR parent.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' 
  AND (action contains 'openprocess' OR param.dst contains 'VirtualAllocEx' OR param.dst contains 'WriteProcessMemory' OR param.dst contains 'CreateRemoteThread') 
  AND target.filename NOT IN ('explorer.exe','svchost.exe') AND NOT file.signer.exists=true
\\Outlook-origin process or its child invoking process-injection APIs into other processes — suggests in-memory backdoor activity or lateral code execution.
\\MITRE: T1055

<Suspicious scheduled task created that launches Outlook or add-in from user-writable path>
action='createprocess' AND filename.dst='schtasks.exe' AND param.dst contains '/create' 
  AND (param.dst contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\AddIns\\' OR param.dst contains '\\AppData\\Local\\Microsoft\\Outlook\\' OR param.dst contains '%temp%') 
  AND NOT (param.dst contains 'SCCM' || param.dst contains 'Microsoft') 
\\Scheduled task created to run Outlook or add-in from user-writable locations — attacker persistence or automated backdoor re-launch.
\\MITRE: T1053.005, T1543

<Outlook launching PowerShell with encoded commands and subsequent network activity>
parent.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' AND action='createprocess' AND filename.dst='powershell.exe' 
  AND param.dst contains '-enc' OR param.dst contains '-EncodedCommand' 
  AND later (network_connect AND direction='outbound' AND ip.dst exists) within 300s
\\Outlook spawning encoded PowerShell which then initiates outbound connections — strong indicator of stealthy execution + C2 launched via mail client context.
\\MITRE: T1059.001, T1071

<Unusual file rename or move of Outlook data files to external share or cloud path>
action='movefile' AND (filepath contains '\\Users\\' AND (filepath endswith '.pst' OR filepath endswith '.ost' OR filepath endswith '.msg')) 
  AND (param.dst contains '\\\\' OR param.dst contains 's3://' OR param.dst contains 'sharepoint' || param.dst contains 'dropbox') 
  AND parent.filename.src NOT IN ('backup.exe','trusted_sync_tool.exe')
\\Moving or copying mailbox/data files to network/cloud destinations by non-backup processes — indicative of data theft/exfil staging.
\\MITRE: T1114, T1537

<High-confidence chain — malicious attachment drop → Outlook executes encoded loader → add-in installed under AppData → periodic outbound beacons>
action='createfile' AND filepath contains '\\AppData\\Local\\Temp\\' AND filepath endswith ('.doc',' .docx','.xls','.xlsm') 
  AND later action='createprocess' AND parent.filename.src='OUTLOOK.EXE' AND filename.dst='powershell.exe' AND param.dst contains '-enc' within 300s 
  AND later action='createfile' AND filepath contains '\\AppData\\Roaming\\Microsoft\\AddIns\\' AND filepath endswith '.dll' within 600s 
  AND later (network_connect AND protocol IN ('HTTP','HTTPS') AND count(network_connect) >= 5 within 3600s by host.id)
\\Sequence: weaponized attachment → Outlook-executed encoded loader → add-in DLL dropped to user AddIns → periodic outbound connections = high-confidence targeted Outlook backdoor activity / persistence + C2.
\\MITRE: T1204.002, T1059.001, T1195, T1071, T1543.003
